<!--
  Example: Seat Reservation and Booking — Nordic Profile
  
  Demonstrates the data elements required to express seat reservation
  policies for long-distance rail services in NeTEx.
  
  Scenario: Two train services on the Oslo–Bergen line (Bergensbanen):
    1. Day train 601 (Oslo S → Bergen) — reservations recommended
    2. Night train 605 (Oslo S → Bergen) — reservations compulsory (sleeper)
  
  Key reservation concepts shown:
    - ServiceFacilitySet with ServiceReservationFacilityList
    - AccommodationFacilityList for sleeper/family carriages
    - JourneyPart → ServiceFacilitySetRef linkage
    - DatedServiceJourney → TrainBlockRef for formation assignment
    - TrainBlock → CompoundTrainRef for physical train composition
    - Train/CompoundTrain for vehicle formation details
-->
